&lt;p&gt;MinIO is the data and memory foundation for enterprise AI. Built for the speed, scale, and economics that AI and analytics demand, AIStor and MemKV unify every layer of the data stack, from agentic and inference context memory to tables and objects across core, edge, and cloud. Trusted by 77% of the Fortune 100, MinIO is redefining how AI factories, intelligent applications, and autonomous agents secure, persist, and unlock the full value of their data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are seeking a strategic, hands-on Accounting Manager who can immediately contribute across core accounting functions. This role is ideal for someone who thrives in a fast-paced, scaling environment and is comfortable operating in partial manual processes while helping to improve them. This position will flex in scope and seniority depending on experience (Sr. Accountant to Manager level), but at its core requires strong execution, ownership, and problem-solving across GL, revenue, and consolidations. This person will also be the primary power user of our accounting systems, primarily Sage Intacct.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;General Ledger &amp;amp; Close&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own and execute key components of the monthly close process&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and review journal entries across all accounting areas including payroll, accruals, and fixed assets&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Perform account reconciliations and flux analysis&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ensure accuracy and completeness of financials in Sage Intacct&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Complete close reconciliations and activities in Floqast&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Validate team member task completion in Floqast&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Revenue Accounting&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support revenue recognition in accordance with ASC606&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Prepare and review revenue schedules, deferred revenue, and related entries&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner cross-functionally to ensure accuracy of billing and revenue data&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Consolidations &amp;amp; Reporting&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Assist with multi-entity consolidations, including intercompany eliminations&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain and improve consolidation processes within Sage Intacct&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Generate financial statements and supporting reports in Sage Intacct&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;Systems &amp;amp; Processes&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage areas requiring manual workflows including all GL postings&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Sage Intacct maintenance including creating departments and GL accounts, update mapping tables across related systems and processes, and update key reports in Sage Intacct&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Help design scalable processes and documentation (SOPs)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Recommend and implement improvements where possible&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with Finance and Operations teams to improve data flows&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support Floqast close/task checklist maintenance in Floqast&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Skills and Experience:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5-8+ years of accounting experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong working knowledge of US GAAP&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience working with incomplete or non-integrated systems&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deep GL accounting experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong ERP proficiency (Sage Intacct, NetSuite, Workday Financials, etc.)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience in SaaS or usage-based revenue models with a working knowledge of revenue recognition (ASC 606)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Experience with consolidations and multi-entity environments&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Comfort handling manual accounting processes with attention to detail&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Ability to operate with a high degree of ownership as an individual contributor&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Exceptional accuracy, organization, and

&lt;section class=&quot;styles--3vx-H&quot; data-ui=&quot;job-description&quot;&gt;
&lt;p class=&quot;p1&quot;&gt;MinIO is the data and memory foundation for enterprise AI. Built for the speed, scale, and economics that AI and analytics demand, AIStor and MemKV unify every layer of the data stack, from agentic and inference context memory to tables and objects across core, edge, and cloud. Trusted by 77% of the Fortune 100, MinIO is redefining how AI factories, intelligent applications, and autonomous agents secure, persist, and unlock the full value of their data.&lt;br&gt;&lt;br&gt;We are looking for a Business Development Representative to join our growing sales team. Based in South Korea, you will serve as MinIO&#39;s primary market presence for inbound and outbound pipeline generation across the Korean market. You will manage and qualify inbound demand, execute targeted outbound prospecting, and work closely with Account Executives to advance opportunities across the data infrastructure and AI storage landscape. This role requires full professional fluency in both Korean and English.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h4&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Inbound Lead Management&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Respond rapidly to all inbound MQLs in your assigned territory (pricing and demo requests, content downloads, AIStor trial downloads, etc.).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Qualify inbound leads for ICP alignment, workload fit, storage scale, environment, and project timing.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedule and confirm qualified meetings for Account Executives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Document all research learnings and call notes clearly in CRM to ensure strong AE handoffs.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Outbound Prospecting&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Research and identify target accounts using intent data, account signals, and MinIO&#39;s intelligence systems.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Execute personalized outbound sequences via email, phone, and LinkedIn targeting infrastructure, data engineering, and AI/ML personas at Korean enterprises.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop strategies to convert MinIO&#39;s open-source user base into commercial customers within the Korean market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with Account Executives and marketing to align outbound efforts with account-based plays and active campaigns.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Live Chat &amp;amp; Digital Engagement&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Serve as a primary responder for website live chat inquiries.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Engage prospects in real time, to understand use cases and urgency.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Convert chat conversations into qualified meetings.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Campaign &amp;amp; Event Follow-Up&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Follow up on leads generated from paid media campaigns targeting the Korean market.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Support pre-event meeting recruitment and post-event follow-up for Korean and broader APAC events.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Schedule meetings tied to webinars, field events, and regional conferences.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide feedback to marketing on lead quality and regional trends.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Pipeline Development&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build multi-threaded outreach into target accounts, engaging both technical and business stakeholders.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide ongoing feedback to sales and marketing on prospect sentiment, objections, and market dynamics specific to Korea.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Maintain Salesforce, HubSpot, and Outreach with accurate, up-to-date activity and qualification data.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Success Metrics&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meetings held with Korean accounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Meeting-to-Stage 1 opportunity conversion rate&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Speed-to-lead for inbound Korean MQLs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;CRM data completeness and accuracy&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
