&lt;h3&gt;Required Qualifications&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Bachelor’s degree in Accounting, Finance, or related field.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8–12+ years of progressive accounting experience, including public accounting experience, and significant w

&lt;section class=&quot;styles--3vx-H&quot; data-ui=&quot;job-description&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MinIO is the data and memory foundation for enterprise AI. Built for the speed, scale, and economics that AI and analytics demand, AIStor and MemKV unify every layer of the data stack, from agentic and inference context memory to tables and objects across core, edge, and cloud. Trusted by 77% of the Fortune 100, MinIO is redefining how AI factories, intelligent applications, and autonomous agents secure, persist, and unlock the full value of their data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We’re seeking a strategic, detail-oriented &lt;strong&gt;Director of FP&amp;amp;A&lt;/strong&gt; to lead our financial planning and analysis function and oversee our business intelligence analyst team. This leader will drive forecasting, budgeting, and reporting processes while also elevating our analytics capabilities to deliver actionable insights to stakeholders across the company.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You’ll be a key partner to the executive team, helping to translate financial and operational data into strategic guidance and resource allocation decisions. The ideal candidate brings a strong FP&amp;amp;A foundation, a sharp analytical mindset, and experience managing a centralized analytics team.&lt;br&gt;&lt;strong&gt;&lt;br&gt;What You Will Do&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Financial Planning &amp;amp; Analysis (FP&amp;amp;A)&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead the company’s annual budgeting, long-range financial planning, and monthly forecasting processes, ensuring alignment with corporate objectives.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Own the preparation, analysis, and presentation of monthly financial reporting packages, including variance analysis, to executive leadership and the board.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop and maintain detailed financial models to support budgeting, forecasting, and business planning processes.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Partner with key departments (e.g., GTM, Product, Operations) to develop financial models and KPIs that guide investment decisions and business growth.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Manage company-wide headcount planning and operating expense (opex) forecasting to ensure alignment with corporate goals.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Lead scenario analysis to support strategic decisions, such as pricing changes, cost structure adjustments, or expansion into new markets.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Provide actionable financial insights and strategic recommendations to senior leadership to drive financial and operational performance.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Oversee the preparation of quarterly and annual financial statements, ensuring compliance with accounting standards and accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Collaborate with the accounting team to ensure timely and accurate closing processes, and review financial statements for consistency and accuracy.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Evaluate financial performance and provide recommendations for improvements in efficiency, profitability, and cost control.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;/section&gt;
&lt;section class=&quot;styles--3vx-H&quot; data-ui=&quot;job-requirements&quot;&gt;
&lt;h4 id=&quot;job-requirements-title&quot;&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Your Skills and Experience&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/h4&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;8+ years of experience in FP&amp;amp;A, financial planning, or corporate finance roles, ideally within high-growth SaaS or tech environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;At least 3 years of experience managing FP&amp;amp;A teams.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Extensive experience in budgeting, financial statement preparation, and variance analysis for senior leadership and boards.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Expertise in building and scaling financial models and forecasts for complex business environments.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Strong understanding of SaaS financial metrics (e.g., ARR, CAC, LTV, gross margin, retention, sales efficiency).&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Proficiency in financial systems (e.g., Sage Intacct) and

&lt;section class=&quot;styles--3vx-H&quot; data-ui=&quot;job-description&quot;&gt;
&lt;p&gt;MinIO is the data and memory foundation for enterprise AI. Built for the speed, scale, and economics that AI and analytics demand, AIStor and MemKV unify every layer of the data stack, from agentic and inference context memory to tables and objects across core, edge, and cloud. Trusted by 77% of the Fortune 100, MinIO is redefining how AI factories, intelligent applications, and autonomous agents secure, persist, and unlock the full value of their data.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The Director, Product Marketing - Analytics Partners will play a pivotal role in shaping how MinIO is positioned within the Databricks ecosystem and the broader hybrid analytics and AI landscape. This role combines deep fluency in the modern data lakehouse, Delta Sharing, and open table formats with hands-on product marketing ownership of MinIO&#39;s most strategic data platform partnership. You will be responsible for understanding how AIStor Table Sharing extends Databricks to on-premises data, and translating that knowledge into differentiated messaging, joint content, and go to market strategies that resonate with data and AI leaders, platform engineers, and the Databricks field teams selling alongside us.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will collaborate with Engineering, Product Management, Sales, Alliances, Corporate Development, and counterparts at Databricks to craft and deliver the narratives that position AIStor as the data platform that unlocks on-premises data for Databricks. Every on-premises table connected through AIStor is a new workload running on Databricks compute, and this role owns the messaging that makes that commercial story land with Databricks account teams and end customers alike.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;What You Will Do:&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Databricks Partnership Narrative: Own the messaging and content that defines MinIO&#39;s role in the Databricks ecosystem across AIStor Table Sharing, Delta Sharing, Unity Catalog, Apache Iceberg™, and Delta Lake. Translate joint engineering work and architectural integration into co-marketing assets, reference architecture content, and customer-facing narratives that position Databricks as the hero with AIStor as the enabling data platform. Navigate across Product and Marketing across both companies to ensure that MinIO features and capabilities are tied to the newest capabilities and offerings from Databricks.&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Executive Presence: Be the face of MinIO&#39;s marketing efforts for the Databricks partnership, representing the joint story at industry events, on webinars, in analyst briefings, and in executive conversations with Databricks and customer leadership.&lt;/li&gt;
