&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Design and deliver field architect curriculum — equipping FAs and Customer Engineers (CEs) with the technical depth and competitive positioning fluency needed to win enterprise deals&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Deliver live and recorded enablement sessions for field architects and, occasionally, non-technical sales audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Develop partner sales curriculum by translating sales and marketing content into structured, teachable modules for partner and reseller audiences&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build core curriculum for customer administrators and operators — covering installation, configuration, management, and troubleshooting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Create use-case &quot;wrappers&quot; that reframe core curriculum content for specific deployment contexts and horizontal use cases, with references to vertical specifics where relevant&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Contribute to special projects requiring hands-on technical skill across a broad range of technologies including Linux, Ansible, Python, Kubernetes, and other core technologies&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Build real-world, use case–driven hands-on labs that establish best practices for deploying and operating MinIO products&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Apply prior experience with competitive storage platforms to inform differentiated, insight-rich training content&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Package labs and content into short, outcome-oriented training modules with videos&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Record engaging videos of modules for MinIO Academy, YouTube, and LinkedIn&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
